ğŸ§ª 4. IngÃ©nierie des Variables

CrÃ©ation dâ€™une nouvelle variable : le ratio dâ€™inscription primaire / secondaire, utile pour analyser les disparitÃ©s dâ€™accÃ¨s.

df["school_enrol_pri_sec_ratio"] = df["school_enrol_primary_pct"] / df["school_enrol_secondary_pct"]

ğŸ¤– 5. ModÃ©lisation et PrÃ©diction

Nous utilisons un modÃ¨le Random Forest Regressor pour prÃ©dire le taux d'inscription scolaire secondaire.

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error

# SÃ©paration des donnÃ©es
X = df.copy()
y = X.pop('school_enrol_secondary_pct')

train_X, val_X, train_y, val_y = train_test_split(X, y, random_state=0)

# ModÃ¨le Random Forest
forest_model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=1)
forest_model.fit(train_X, train_y)

# PrÃ©dictions
y_preds = forest_model.predict(val_X)

print("Mean Absolute Error:", mean_absolute_error(val_y, y_preds))

